    "Hence h(y) ⊆ R ′ i [h(x)], so h(x)R ′℘ i h(y), which with h(y) ̸ ∈ X implies R ′℘ i (h(x)) ̸ ⊆ X. Conversely, suppose R ′℘ i (h(x)) ̸ ⊆ X, so there is a Y such that h(x)R ′℘ i Y, i.e., Y ⊆ R ′ i [h(x)], and Y ̸ ∈ X.",
    "Then by refinability for X and the fact that (AtF) ℘ is atomic, Y ̸ ∈ X implies that there is a minimal point B in (AtF) ℘ such that B ⊑ ′℘ Y, i.e., B ⊆ Y, andB ̸ ∈ X.",
    "That B is a minimal point in (AtF) ℘ means that B = {b} for a b in AtF.",
